cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to improve the quality of periocular iris images captured from cell phone selfies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with machine learning techniques to classify the sex of the subject based on the iris images, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the challenges of data acquisition and privacy concerns, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the potential applications of selfie soft biometrics in marketing and online banking, which could fall under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper deals with iris recognition, which could fall under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
